{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019Ee8EMtbLot62movK9HktZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Improvement Plan — Iteration 6\n     2→\n     3→## Why Iteration 5 Failed\n     4→\n     5→The iteration 4 plan correctly diagnosed all three failures and proposed five changes, but the critical ones (origin tracking, continuation join protection, embedding-based baseHeading, distributed structural bonus) were not implemented. The code still has:\n     6→- No `origin` field on candidates — continuation join protection can't distinguish joins from singles\n     7→- `baseHeading = candidates.find(isStructuralHeading)` — still purely positional\n     8→- `structuralBonus` still exclusive to `firstStructuralHeading` (+0.10, one candidate only)\n     9→\n    10→This iteration re-proposes the essential changes with tighter implementation specifications.\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Root Cause Analysis\n    15→\n    16→### Failure 1: `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander` → `''`\n    17→\n    18→The title is split across two OCR lines. The 2-line join passes hard filters but dedup removes it: the single-line fragment `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce` is a substring and shorter, so the join is discarded. The surviving partial likely falls below threshold (no ALL_CAPS bonus, no structural bonus).\n    19→\n    20→**Root cause:** Dedup's \"shorter wins\" rule cannot distinguish \"title + ingredient run-on\" (where shorter is correct) from \"first half of split title + complete title join\" (where longer is correct). The `& Coriander` continuation is the discriminating signal.\n    21→\n    22→### Failure 2: `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS` → `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS`\n    23→\n    24→Both titles pass `isStructuralHeading`. But only the first gets `structuralBonus` (+0.10). This inflates `bestBaseScore`, which raises `threshold = bestBaseScore × 0.7`. The second title has only `allCapsBonus` (+0.08) and no position boost (at ~65% depth), so it falls below the inflated threshold. The multi-title guard never fires because the second title is already filtered out.\n    25→\n    26→**Root cause:** `structuralBonus` leaks into `bestBaseScore`, raising the bar so high that equally-valid structural headings without the bonus can't pass. The iteration 3 fix for position-boost leakage was not extended to bonus leakage.\n    27→\n    28→### Failure 3: `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)` → `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)`\n    29→\n    30→The garbled OCR fragment `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)` appears earlier in the document and passes `isStructuralHeading` (all sig words ≥ 4 uppercase letters). Being the first positional match, it becomes `baseHeading`, gets `structuralBonus` (+0.10), and hijacks the continuation extension logic. The correct title's 2-line join is also killed by dedup (same mechanism as Failure 1).\n    31→\n    32→**Root cause:** `baseHeading` selection is purely positional with no quality signal. A garbled OCR fragment that happens to satisfy `isStructuralHeading` can claim the structural heading slot over the real title.\n    33→\n    34→---\n    35→\n    36→## Proposed Changes\n    37→\n    38→### Change 1: Track candidate origin in `buildCandidates`\n    39→\n    40→**What:** Add an `origin` field (`\"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\"`) to candidate objects. This is pure metadata — no behavioral change — but is required by Change 2.\n    41→\n    42→**Where:** `title-extractor.ts`, `buildCandidates` function (lines 163–231).\n    43→\n    44→**Before:**\n    45→```ts\n    46→function buildCandidates(\n    47→  lines: Array<string>\n    48→): Array<{ text: string; position: number }> {\n    49→```\n    50→\n    51→**After:**\n    52→```ts\n    53→export type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n    54→\n    55→function buildCandidates(\n    56→  lines: Array<string>\n    57→): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→Tag each `candidates.push(...)` call:\n    61→- Line 187: `candidates.push({ text: line.text, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });`\n    62→- Line 198: `candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });`\n    63→- Line 210: `candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });`\n    64→\n    65→Propagate the `origin` field through `scored` and `selected` arrays (add to their type signatures).\n    66→\n    67→**Impact:** None by itself. Enables Change 2.\n    68→\n    69→---\n    70→\n    71→### Change 2: Protect continuation joins from dedup (fixes Failures 1 and 3-secondary)\n    72→\n    73→**What:** Before the dedup filter, remove single-line candidates that are a prefix of a surviving multi-line join whose continuation part begins with a continuation character (`/`, `&`, `+`, `:`, `(`). This prevents the \"shorter wins\" rule from destroying valid title joins.\n    74→\n    75→**Where:** New block inserted between the structural-heading prefix removal (line 352) and the dedup filter (line 359). The dedup block itself is NOT modified (respecting the guard comment).\n    76→\n    77→**Logic:**\n    78→```ts\n    79→// Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join survived the threshold and\n    80→// its second part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line\n    81→// prefix so dedup can't destroy the complete join.\n    82→const survivingJoins = selected.filter(\n    83→  (s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\"\n    84→);\n    85→if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n    86→  selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n    87→    if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n    88→    const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n    89→    return !survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n    90→      const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n    91→      if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n    92→      const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n    93→      return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n    94→    });\n    95→  });\n    96→}\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→**Why safe for Pierogi Ruskie:** The join `\"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\"` has a continuation starting with `\"200g\"` — a digit, not a continuation character. The prefix `\"Pierogi Ruskie\"` is preserved, dedup correctly picks it. No behavioral change for non-continuation joins.\n   100→\n   101→**Expected impact:** Fixes Failure 1 — the join `\"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\"` is protected (continuation starts with `&`). Also fixes the secondary issue in Failure 3 — the join `\"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\"` is protected (continuation starts with `/`).\n   102→\n   103→---\n   104→\n   105→### Change 3: Exclude `structuralBonus` from threshold computation (fixes Failure 2)\n   106→\n   107→**What:** Compute `bestBaseScore` using `rawScore + allCapsBonus` only, excluding `structuralBonus` (and `firstHeadingBonus` if Change 4 adds one). The structural bonus still helps the heading win the ranking, but does not inflate the threshold that other candidates must pass.\n   108→\n   109→**Where:** Scoring loop and threshold computation (lines 320–332).\n   110→\n   111→**Before:**\n   112→```ts\n   113→const baseScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   114→// ...\n   115→const bestBaseScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.baseScore));\n   116→const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestBaseScore * 0.7);\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→**After:** Add a new field `thresholdScore` that excludes structural bonus:\n   120→```ts\n   121→const baseScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   122→const thresholdScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus; // no structural bonus\n   123→// ...\n   124→const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n   125→const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n   126→```\n   127→\n   128→**Why this works:** On the Finnish Flatbreads page, `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS` has `rawScore ≈ X`, `allCapsBonus = 0.08`, `structuralBonus = 0.10`. Previously `bestBaseScore = X + 0.18` and `threshold = (X + 0.18) × 0.7`. Now `bestThresholdScore = X + 0.08` and `threshold = (X + 0.08) × 0.7`. The second title with `score = X' + 0.08` (similar rawScore, same allCapsBonus) easily clears this lower bar.\n   129→\n   130→**Why safe:** The structural bonus still contributes to `score` and `baseScore` for ranking purposes — it just doesn't inflate the threshold. Single-recipe pages are unaffected because there's only one candidate to rank.\n   131→\n   132→**Expected impact:** Fixes Failure 2. Both Finnish titles pass the threshold; the multi-title guard (`allCapsSelected.length >= 2`) fires and returns both.\n   133→\n   134→---\n   135→\n   136→### Change 4: Select `baseHeading` by embedding quality, not position (fixes Failure 3-primary)\n   137→\n   138→**What:** Defer `baseHeading` selection until after embeddings are computed. Instead of `candidates.find(isStructuralHeading)` (first positional match), pick the structural heading candidate with the highest `rawScore`.\n   139→\n   140→**Where:** Move structural heading selection from lines 278–292 to after the scoring loop (after line 323).\n   141→\n   142→**Before (line 278):**\n   143→```ts\n   144→const baseHeading = candidates.find(isStructuralHeading);\n   145→```\n   146→\n   147→**After (after scoring loop, before threshold computation):**\n   148→```ts\n   149→// Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n   150→// This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\n   151→const structuralCandidateScores = scored.filter((s) => {\n   152→  const orig = candidates.find((c) => c.text === s.text);\n   153→  return orig && isStructuralHeading(orig);\n   154→});\n   155→const bestStructural = structuralCandidateScores.length > 0\n   156→  ? structuralCandidateScores.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n   157→  : null;\n   158→const baseHeading = bestStructural\n   159→  ? candidates.find((c) => c.text === bestStructural.text)\n   160→  : undefined;\n   161→```\n   162→\n   163→This requires restructuring the scoring loop slightly: compute `rawScore` first (without bonuses), then select `baseHeading`, then assign bonuses in a second pass. The restructuring adds no new embedding calls.\n   164→\n   165→**Restructured scoring flow:**\n   166→```ts\n   167→// Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates\n   168→const rawScored = [];\n   169→for (const candidate of candidates) {\n   170→  const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n   171→  const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n   172→  const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n   173→  const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n   174→  const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n   175→  rawScored.push({ ...candidate, rawScore, embedding });\n   176→}\n   177→\n   178→// Select baseHeading by rawScore quality\n   179→const structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\n   180→const bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n   181→  ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n   182→  : null;\n   183→const baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n   184→\n   185→// Derive firstStructuralHeading (continuation extension) — same logic as before\n   186→const firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n   187→  rawScored.find((c) => {\n   188→    if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n   189→    const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   190→    const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n   191→    return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n   192→  }) ?? baseHeading\n   193→);\n   194→\n   195→// Pass 2: apply bonuses\n   196→const scored = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n   197→  const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n   198→  const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5 ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2) : 1.0;\n   199→  const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4 ? 0.08 : 0;\n   200→  const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n   201→  const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n   202→  const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   203→  const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   204→  return { ...rs, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n   205→});\n   206→```\n   207→\n   208→**Why this works:** `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)` is garbled — its MiniLM embedding will have low similarity to the title reference (\"recipe name, dish title\") compared to `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK`, a plausible recipe title. The correct heading wins `baseHeading`, continuation extension fires for the `/` join, and the structural bonus goes to the right candidate.\n   209→\n   210→**Performance:** Zero additional embedding calls. Same candidates, same embeddings, just reordered logic.\n   211→\n   212→**Expected impact:** Fixes the primary bug in Failure 3.\n   213→\n   214→---\n   215→\n   216→### Change 5: OCR truncation cross-validation (defense-in-depth for Failure 3)\n   217→\n   218→**What:** After selecting `bestStructural` in Change 4, add a lightweight cross-validation: if a significant word in one structural heading is a strict suffix of a significant word in another structural heading, penalize the shorter-word candidate's rawScore by -0.15. This catches `FRON` being a suffix of `SAFFRON`.\n   219→\n   220→**Where:** Between structural candidate filtering and `bestStructural` selection in Change 4.\n   221→\n   222→**Logic:**\n   223→```ts\n   224→// Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n   225→// if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled\n   226→for (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n   227→  const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   228→  for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n   229→    if (other === sc) continue;\n   230→    const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   231→    const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n   232→      otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n   233→    );\n   234→    if (hasTruncation) {\n   235→      sc.rawScore -= 0.15;\n   236→      break;\n   237→    }\n   238→  }\n   239→}\n   240→```\n   241→\n   242→**Why safe:** Only fires when two structural headings share a suffix relationship — extremely unlikely to produce false positives. On the Finnish page, `FLATBREADS` appears in both titles but `ow !== w` prevents self-matching and neither is a suffix of the other.\n   243→\n   244→**Expected impact:** Additional safety for Failure 3. Even if embeddings alone don't sufficiently separate the garbled candidate, the -0.15 penalty ensures it loses.\n   245→\n   246→---\n   247→\n   248→## Summary\n   249→\n   250→| Change | Fixes | Risk | Scope |\n   251→|---|---|---|---|\n   252→| 1. Track `origin` field | Enables #2 | None (metadata only) | `buildCandidates` return type |\n   253→| 2. Protect continuation joins | F1, F3 secondary | Low — continuation char guard | New block before dedup |\n   254→| 3. Exclude structural bonus from threshold | F2 | Low — bonus still helps ranking | Threshold computation (2 lines) |\n   255→| 4. Embedding-quality baseHeading | F3 primary | Low — better signal, same data | Restructure scoring into 2 passes |\n   256→| 5. OCR truncation penalty | F3 defense | Very low — strict cross-match only | New block in structural selection |\n   257→\n   258→### Performance\n   259→\n   260→- **Zero additional embedding calls.** All changes reorder existing logic or add O(25²) string comparisons.\n   261→- **No new dependencies.** All changes within `title-extractor.ts`.\n   262→- **Mobile-safe.** Well under the 10-second budget.\n   263→\n   264→### Expected Accuracy\n   265→\n   266→- **F1 (Baked Eggs):** Fixed by Changes 1+2. Join is protected from dedup → `\"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\"` survives.\n   267→- **F2 (Finnish Flatbreads):** Fixed by Change 3. Threshold no longer inflated by structural bonus → both titles pass → multi-title guard joins them with `+`.\n   268→- **F3 (Saffron Wheat Buns):** Fixed by Changes 4+5 (correct baseHeading) + Changes 1+2 (correct join protected) → `\"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\"` is returned.\n   269→\n   270→### Regression Risks\n   271→\n   272→- **Pierogi Ruskie:** Change 2 does NOT protect this join (continuation starts with `\"200g\"`, a digit). Dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n   273→- **ARAYES SHRAK:** Existing structural heading prefix removal (lines 337–352) still fires. Change 2 adds a parallel protection path but doesn't conflict.\n   274→- **MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD / OVERNIGHT PIZZA DOUGH:** Single structural headings. Change 3 doesn't affect threshold when there's only one strong candidate. Change 4 picks the same heading (only one structural candidate).\n   275→\n   276→### Key Difference from Iteration 4 Plan\n   277→\n   278→The iteration 4 plan proposed essentially the same changes but they weren't implemented. This plan:\n   279→1. **Makes the restructuring explicit** — Change 4 spells out the 2-pass scoring flow so it's clear how to restructure without breaking the existing logic.\n   280→2. **Separates threshold from ranking** — Change 3 uses a dedicated `thresholdScore` field rather than trying to redistribute bonuses, which is simpler to implement correctly.\n   281→3. **Emphasizes the dependency chain** — Changes must be implemented in order: 1 → 2, and 4 → 5. Change 3 is independent. The scoring restructure in Change 4 is the most invasive and should be implemented carefully.\n   282→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"387de5e0-40bd-48c5-805c-791e6708a784","uuid":"af4f55c1-b5dc-4120-876b-4d19069bd57e","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/5-218113e/improvement-plan.md","content":"# Improvement Plan — Iteration 6\n\n## Why Iteration 5 Failed\n\nThe iteration 4 plan correctly diagnosed all three failures and proposed five changes, but the critical ones (origin tracking, continuation join protection, embedding-based baseHeading, distributed structural bonus) were not implemented. The code still has:\n- No `origin` field on candidates — continuation join protection can't distinguish joins from singles\n- `baseHeading = candidates.find(isStructuralHeading)` — still purely positional\n- `structuralBonus` still exclusive to `firstStructuralHeading` (+0.10, one candidate only)\n\nThis iteration re-proposes the essential changes with tighter implementation specifications.\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\n### Failure 1: `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander` → `''`\n\nThe title is split across two OCR lines. The 2-line join passes hard filters but dedup removes it: the single-line fragment `Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce` is a substring and shorter, so the join is discarded. The surviving partial likely falls below threshold (no ALL_CAPS bonus, no structural bonus).\n\n**Root cause:** Dedup's \"shorter wins\" rule cannot distinguish \"title + ingredient run-on\" (where shorter is correct) from \"first half of split title + complete title join\" (where longer is correct). The `& Coriander` continuation is the discriminating signal.\n\n### Failure 2: `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS` → `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS`\n\nBoth titles pass `isStructuralHeading`. But only the first gets `structuralBonus` (+0.10). This inflates `bestBaseScore`, which raises `threshold = bestBaseScore × 0.7`. The second title has only `allCapsBonus` (+0.08) and no position boost (at ~65% depth), so it falls below the inflated threshold. The multi-title guard never fires because the second title is already filtered out.\n\n**Root cause:** `structuralBonus` leaks into `bestBaseScore`, raising the bar so high that equally-valid structural headings without the bonus can't pass. The iteration 3 fix for position-boost leakage was not extended to bonus leakage.\n\n### Failure 3: `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)` → `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)`\n\nThe garbled OCR fragment `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)` appears earlier in the document and passes `isStructuralHeading` (all sig words ≥ 4 uppercase letters). Being the first positional match, it becomes `baseHeading`, gets `structuralBonus` (+0.10), and hijacks the continuation extension logic. The correct title's 2-line join is also killed by dedup (same mechanism as Failure 1).\n\n**Root cause:** `baseHeading` selection is purely positional with no quality signal. A garbled OCR fragment that happens to satisfy `isStructuralHeading` can claim the structural heading slot over the real title.\n\n---\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### Change 1: Track candidate origin in `buildCandidates`\n\n**What:** Add an `origin` field (`\"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\"`) to candidate objects. This is pure metadata — no behavioral change — but is required by Change 2.\n\n**Where:** `title-extractor.ts`, `buildCandidates` function (lines 163–231).\n\n**Before:**\n```ts\nfunction buildCandidates(\n  lines: Array<string>\n): Array<{ text: string; position: number }> {\n```\n\n**After:**\n```ts\nexport type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n\nfunction buildCandidates(\n  lines: Array<string>\n): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n```\n\nTag each `candidates.push(...)` call:\n- Line 187: `candidates.push({ text: line.text, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });`\n- Line 198: `candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });`\n- Line 210: `candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });`\n\nPropagate the `origin` field through `scored` and `selected` arrays (add to their type signatures).\n\n**Impact:** None by itself. Enables Change 2.\n\n---\n\n### Change 2: Protect continuation joins from dedup (fixes Failures 1 and 3-secondary)\n\n**What:** Before the dedup filter, remove single-line candidates that are a prefix of a surviving multi-line join whose continuation part begins with a continuation character (`/`, `&`, `+`, `:`, `(`). This prevents the \"shorter wins\" rule from destroying valid title joins.\n\n**Where:** New block inserted between the structural-heading prefix removal (line 352) and the dedup filter (line 359). The dedup block itself is NOT modified (respecting the guard comment).\n\n**Logic:**\n```ts\n// Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join survived the threshold and\n// its second part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line\n// prefix so dedup can't destroy the complete join.\nconst survivingJoins = selected.filter(\n  (s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\"\n);\nif (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n  selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n    if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n    const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n    return !survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n      const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n      if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n      const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n      return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n    });\n  });\n}\n```\n\n**Why safe for Pierogi Ruskie:** The join `\"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\"` has a continuation starting with `\"200g\"` — a digit, not a continuation character. The prefix `\"Pierogi Ruskie\"` is preserved, dedup correctly picks it. No behavioral change for non-continuation joins.\n\n**Expected impact:** Fixes Failure 1 — the join `\"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\"` is protected (continuation starts with `&`). Also fixes the secondary issue in Failure 3 — the join `\"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\"` is protected (continuation starts with `/`).\n\n---\n\n### Change 3: Exclude `structuralBonus` from threshold computation (fixes Failure 2)\n\n**What:** Compute `bestBaseScore` using `rawScore + allCapsBonus` only, excluding `structuralBonus` (and `firstHeadingBonus` if Change 4 adds one). The structural bonus still helps the heading win the ranking, but does not inflate the threshold that other candidates must pass.\n\n**Where:** Scoring loop and threshold computation (lines 320–332).\n\n**Before:**\n```ts\nconst baseScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n// ...\nconst bestBaseScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.baseScore));\nconst threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestBaseScore * 0.7);\n```\n\n**After:** Add a new field `thresholdScore` that excludes structural bonus:\n```ts\nconst baseScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\nconst thresholdScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus; // no structural bonus\n// ...\nconst bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\nconst threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n```\n\n**Why this works:** On the Finnish Flatbreads page, `FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS` has `rawScore ≈ X`, `allCapsBonus = 0.08`, `structuralBonus = 0.10`. Previously `bestBaseScore = X + 0.18` and `threshold = (X + 0.18) × 0.7`. Now `bestThresholdScore = X + 0.08` and `threshold = (X + 0.08) × 0.7`. The second title with `score = X' + 0.08` (similar rawScore, same allCapsBonus) easily clears this lower bar.\n\n**Why safe:** The structural bonus still contributes to `score` and `baseScore` for ranking purposes — it just doesn't inflate the threshold. Single-recipe pages are unaffected because there's only one candidate to rank.\n\n**Expected impact:** Fixes Failure 2. Both Finnish titles pass the threshold; the multi-title guard (`allCapsSelected.length >= 2`) fires and returns both.\n\n---\n\n### Change 4: Select `baseHeading` by embedding quality, not position (fixes Failure 3-primary)\n\n**What:** Defer `baseHeading` selection until after embeddings are computed. Instead of `candidates.find(isStructuralHeading)` (first positional match), pick the structural heading candidate with the highest `rawScore`.\n\n**Where:** Move structural heading selection from lines 278–292 to after the scoring loop (after line 323).\n\n**Before (line 278):**\n```ts\nconst baseHeading = candidates.find(isStructuralHeading);\n```\n\n**After (after scoring loop, before threshold computation):**\n```ts\n// Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n// This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\nconst structuralCandidateScores = scored.filter((s) => {\n  const orig = candidates.find((c) => c.text === s.text);\n  return orig && isStructuralHeading(orig);\n});\nconst bestStructural = structuralCandidateScores.length > 0\n  ? structuralCandidateScores.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n  : null;\nconst baseHeading = bestStructural\n  ? candidates.find((c) => c.text === bestStructural.text)\n  : undefined;\n```\n\nThis requires restructuring the scoring loop slightly: compute `rawScore` first (without bonuses), then select `baseHeading`, then assign bonuses in a second pass. The restructuring adds no new embedding calls.\n\n**Restructured scoring flow:**\n```ts\n// Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates\nconst rawScored = [];\nfor (const candidate of candidates) {\n  const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n  const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n  const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n  const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n  const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n  rawScored.push({ ...candidate, rawScore, embedding });\n}\n\n// Select baseHeading by rawScore quality\nconst structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\nconst bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n  ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n  : null;\nconst baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n\n// Derive firstStructuralHeading (continuation extension) — same logic as before\nconst firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n  rawScored.find((c) => {\n    if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n    const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n    const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n    return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n  }) ?? baseHeading\n);\n\n// Pass 2: apply bonuses\nconst scored = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n  const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n  const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5 ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2) : 1.0;\n  const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4 ? 0.08 : 0;\n  const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n  const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n  const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n  const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n  return { ...rs, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n});\n```\n\n**Why this works:** `FRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION 1)` is garbled — its MiniLM embedding will have low similarity to the title reference (\"recipe name, dish title\") compared to `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK`, a plausible recipe title. The correct heading wins `baseHeading`, continuation extension fires for the `/` join, and the structural bonus goes to the right candidate.\n\n**Performance:** Zero additional embedding calls. Same candidates, same embeddings, just reordered logic.\n\n**Expected impact:** Fixes the primary bug in Failure 3.\n\n---\n\n### Change 5: OCR truncation cross-validation (defense-in-depth for Failure 3)\n\n**What:** After selecting `bestStructural` in Change 4, add a lightweight cross-validation: if a significant word in one structural heading is a strict suffix of a significant word in another structural heading, penalize the shorter-word candidate's rawScore by -0.15. This catches `FRON` being a suffix of `SAFFRON`.\n\n**Where:** Between structural candidate filtering and `bestStructural` selection in Change 4.\n\n**Logic:**\n```ts\n// Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n// if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled\nfor (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n  const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n  for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n    if (other === sc) continue;\n    const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n    const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n      otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n    );\n    if (hasTruncation) {\n      sc.rawScore -= 0.15;\n      break;\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Why safe:** Only fires when two structural headings share a suffix relationship — extremely unlikely to produce false positives. On the Finnish page, `FLATBREADS` appears in both titles but `ow !== w` prevents self-matching and neither is a suffix of the other.\n\n**Expected impact:** Additional safety for Failure 3. Even if embeddings alone don't sufficiently separate the garbled candidate, the -0.15 penalty ensures it loses.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Change | Fixes | Risk | Scope |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1. Track `origin` field | Enables #2 | None (metadata only) | `buildCandidates` return type |\n| 2. Protect continuation joins | F1, F3 secondary | Low — continuation char guard | New block before dedup |\n| 3. Exclude structural bonus from threshold | F2 | Low — bonus still helps ranking | Threshold computation (2 lines) |\n| 4. Embedding-quality baseHeading | F3 primary | Low — better signal, same data | Restructure scoring into 2 passes |\n| 5. OCR truncation penalty | F3 defense | Very low — strict cross-match only | New block in structural selection |\n\n### Performance\n\n- **Zero additional embedding calls.** All changes reorder existing logic or add O(25²) string comparisons.\n- **No new dependencies.** All changes within `title-extractor.ts`.\n- **Mobile-safe.** Well under the 10-second budget.\n\n### Expected Accuracy\n\n- **F1 (Baked Eggs):** Fixed by Changes 1+2. Join is protected from dedup → `\"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\"` survives.\n- **F2 (Finnish Flatbreads):** Fixed by Change 3. Threshold no longer inflated by structural bonus → both titles pass → multi-title guard joins them with `+`.\n- **F3 (Saffron Wheat Buns):** Fixed by Changes 4+5 (correct baseHeading) + Changes 1+2 (correct join protected) → `\"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\"` is returned.\n\n### Regression Risks\n\n- **Pierogi Ruskie:** Change 2 does NOT protect this join (continuation starts with `\"200g\"`, a digit). Dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n- **ARAYES SHRAK:** Existing structural heading prefix removal (lines 337–352) still fires. Change 2 adds a parallel protection path but doesn't conflict.\n- **MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD / OVERNIGHT PIZZA DOUGH:** Single structural headings. Change 3 doesn't affect threshold when there's only one strong candidate. Change 4 picks the same heading (only one structural candidate).\n\n### Key Difference from Iteration 4 Plan\n\nThe iteration 4 plan proposed essentially the same changes but they weren't implemented. This plan:\n1. **Makes the restructuring explicit** — Change 4 spells out the 2-pass scoring flow so it's clear how to restructure without breaking the existing logic.\n2. **Separates threshold from ranking** — Change 3 uses a dedicated `thresholdScore` field rather than trying to redistribute bonuses, which is simpler to implement correctly.\n3. **Emphasizes the dependency chain** — Changes must be implemented in order: 1 → 2, and 4 → 5. Change 3 is independent. The scoring restructure in Change 4 is the most invasive and should be implemented carefully.\n","numLines":282,"startLine":1,"totalLines":282}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WjWD943rj6etJ4sjtS23i4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Title Extraction\n     3→ * Extracts potential recipe title from OCR text using heuristics or semantic embeddings\n     4→ */\n     5→\n     6→import { cosineSimilarity } from \"./embeddings\";\n     7→\n     8→export type EmbedFn = (text: string) => Promise<Array<number>>;\n     9→\n    10→const TITLE_REFERENCE =\n    11→  \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\";\n    12→const HEADER_REFERENCE =\n    13→  \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\";\n    14→const NOISE_REFERENCE =\n    15→  \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\";\n    16→\n    17→/**\n    18→ * Measurement units commonly found in ingredient lists\n    19→ */\n    20→const MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS = [\n    21→  \"cup\",\n    22→  \"cups\",\n    23→  \"tbsp\",\n    24→  \"tsp\",\n    25→  \"tablespoon\",\n    26→  \"teaspoon\",\n    27→  \"oz\",\n    28→  \"lb\",\n    29→  \"gram\",\n    30→  \"grams\",\n    31→  \"kg\",\n    32→  \"ml\",\n    33→  \"liter\",\n    34→  \"pinch\",\n    35→  \"dash\",\n    36→  \"handful\",\n    37→];\n    38→\n    39→/**\n    40→ * Patterns that identify recipe metadata lines (not titles)\n    41→ */\n    42→const METADATA_PATTERNS = [\n    43→  /^(SERVES?|MAKES?|YIELDS?)\\b/i,\n    44→  /^(PREP(ARATION)?|COOK(ING)?|PROOF|RISING|FERMENTATION|REST(ING)?)\\s*(AND\\s*)?(COOK(ING)?)?\\s*TIME/i,\n    45→  /^SAMPLE\\s+SCHEDULE\\b/i,\n    46→  /^BULK\\s+FERMENTATION\\b/i,\n    47→  /^(THIS\\s+RECIPE\\s+)?MAKES\\b/i,\n    48→];\n    49→\n    50→/**\n    51→ * Single-word non-title words — standalone OCR fragments unlikely to be recipe titles\n    52→ */\n    53→const NON_TITLE_WORDS = new Set([\n    54→  \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"are\", \"was\",\n    55→  \"has\", \"his\", \"her\", \"its\", \"our\", \"who\", \"how\", \"may\", \"new\", \"now\",\n    56→  \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\", \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n    57→  \"buns\", \"with\",\n    58→]);\n    59→\n    60→function looksLikeIngredient(line: string): boolean {\n    61→  const lowerLine = line.toLowerCase();\n    62→  return MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => lowerLine.includes(pattern));\n    63→}\n    64→\n    65→function startsWithNumber(line: string): boolean {\n    66→  return /^\\s*\\d/.test(line);\n    67→}\n    68→\n    69→function isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n    70→  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n    71→  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n    72→}\n    73→\n    74→function looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n    75→  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n    76→}\n    77→\n    78→function isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n    79→  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n    80→  if (letters.length < 2) return true;\n    81→\n    82→  // Check vowel ratio — English/Polish text typically has 30–50% vowels\n    83→  const vowels = letters.replace(/[^aeiouAEIOUyYąęóĄĘÓ]/g, \"\").length;\n    84→  const vowelRatio = vowels / letters.length;\n    85→  if (vowelRatio < 0.15 || vowelRatio > 0.85) return true;\n    86→\n    87→  // Single orphaned word ≤3 letters that isn't a common word\n    88→  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n    89→  const COMMON_SHORT = new Set([\n    90→    \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"had\", \"her\",\n    91→    \"was\", \"one\", \"our\", \"out\", \"are\", \"has\", \"his\", \"how\", \"its\", \"may\",\n    92→    \"new\", \"now\", \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"who\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\",\n    93→    \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n    94→  ]);\n    95→  if (words.length === 1 && letters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n    96→    return true;\n    97→  }\n    98→\n    99→  // Recipe titles never start with a lowercase letter\n   100→  if (/^[a-z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n   101→    return true;\n   102→  }\n   103→\n   104→  // Mid-text sentence boundary (\". \" followed by a letter) — body text fragment spliced from multiple sentences\n   105→  const trimmed = text.trim();\n   106→  if (/\\.\\s+[a-zA-Z]/.test(trimmed) && !trimmed.endsWith(\")\")) {\n   107→    return true;\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  // Multi-word candidate containing a garbled OCR fragment: a short lowercase word that isn't a known short word\n   111→  if (words.length >= 2) {\n   112→    const commonShort2 = new Set([\n   113→      \"a\", \"i\", \"of\", \"or\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"is\", \"it\", \"an\",\n   114→      \"as\", \"at\", \"by\", \"do\", \"go\", \"if\", \"no\", \"so\", \"up\", \"we\",\n   115→      \"w\", \"z\",  // Polish prepositions\n   116→    ]);\n   117→    const hasGarbledWord = words.some(\n   118→      (w) =>\n   119→        /^[a-z]/.test(w) &&\n   120→        w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\").length <= 2 &&\n   121→        !commonShort2.has(w.toLowerCase())\n   122→    );\n   123→    if (hasGarbledWord) {\n   124→      return true;\n   125→    }\n   126→  }\n   127→\n   128→  return false;\n   129→}\n   130→\n   131→function passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n   132→  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n   133→  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n   134→  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n   135→  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n   136→  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n   137→  // Single-word non-title fragments\n   138→  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n   139→  if (words.length === 1 && NON_TITLE_WORDS.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) return false;\n   140→  return true;\n   141→}\n   142→\n   143→/**\n   144→ * Detect initial burst of short garbled lines.\n   145→ * Returns the index of the first non-garbled or long line.\n   146→ */\n   147→function findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n   148→  let i = 0;\n   149→  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text)) {\n   150→    i++;\n   151→  }\n   152→  return i;\n   153→}\n   154→\n   155→function wordCount(text: string): number {\n   156→  return text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 0).length;\n   157→}\n   158→\n   159→/**\n   160→ * Build candidate strings from lines: single lines plus multi-line joins (2-3 consecutive).\n   161→ * Skips initial burst of short garbled lines. Scans all remaining lines. Caps at 25.\n   162→ */\n   163→export type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n   164→\n   165→function buildCandidates(\n   166→  lines: Array<string>\n   167→): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n   168→  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   169→\n   170→  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n   171→    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n   172→    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n   173→      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n   174→    }\n   175→  }\n   176→\n   177→  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n   178→  const candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> = [];\n   179→  const seen = new Set<string>();\n   180→\n   181→  for (let i = burstEnd; i < nonEmptyLines.length; i++) {\n   182→    const line = nonEmptyLines[i];\n   183→\n   184→    // Single line\n   185→    if (passesHardFilters(line.text)) {\n   186→      const norm = line.text.toLowerCase();\n   187→      if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   188→        seen.add(norm);\n   189→        candidates.push({ text: line.text, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n   190→      }\n   191→    }\n   192→\n   193→    // 2-line join\n   194→    if (i + 1 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n   195→      const joined2 = `${line.text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text}`;\n   196→      if (passesHardFilters(joined2)) {\n   197→        const norm = joined2.toLowerCase();\n   198→        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   199→          seen.add(norm);\n   200→          candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });\n   201→        }\n   202→      }\n   203→    }\n   204→\n   205→    // 3-line join\n   206→    if (i + 2 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n   207→      const joined3 = `${line.text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 2].text}`;\n   208→      if (passesHardFilters(joined3)) {\n   209→        const norm = joined3.toLowerCase();\n   210→        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   211→          seen.add(norm);\n   212→          candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });\n   213→        }\n   214→      }\n   215→    }\n   216→  }\n   217→\n   218→  // Pre-filter to 25 before embedding calls: prefer ALL_CAPS and short candidates.\n   219→  // Position-based scoring handles final ranking.\n   220→  if (candidates.length > 25) {\n   221→    const prioritized = candidates.slice().sort((a, b) => {\n   222→      const aAllCaps = isAllCaps(a.text) ? 0 : 1;\n   223→      const bAllCaps = isAllCaps(b.text) ? 0 : 1;\n   224→      if (aAllCaps !== bAllCaps) return aAllCaps - bAllCaps;\n   225→      const aShort = wordCount(a.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n   226→      const bShort = wordCount(b.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n   227→      return aShort - bShort;\n   228→    });\n   229→    return prioritized.slice(0, 25);\n   230→  }\n   231→\n   232→  return candidates;\n   233→}\n   234→\n   235→// Module-level cache for reference embeddings\n   236→let cachedTitleRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   237→let cachedHeaderRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   238→let cachedNoiseRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   239→\n   240→export function _resetEmbeddingCacheForTests(): void {\n   241→  cachedTitleRefEmbedding = null;\n   242→  cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = null;\n   243→  cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = null;\n   244→}\n   245→\n   246→export async function extractTitleWithEmbeddings(\n   247→  text: string,\n   248→  embed: EmbedFn\n   249→): Promise<string | undefined> {\n   250→  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n   251→    return undefined;\n   252→  }\n   253→\n   254→  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\");\n   255→  const candidates = buildCandidates(lines);\n   256→\n   257→  if (candidates.length === 0) {\n   258→    return undefined;\n   259→  }\n   260→\n   261→  // Cache reference embeddings\n   262→  if (!cachedTitleRefEmbedding) {\n   263→    cachedTitleRefEmbedding = await embed(TITLE_REFERENCE);\n   264→  }\n   265→  if (!cachedHeaderRefEmbedding) {\n   266→    cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = await embed(HEADER_REFERENCE);\n   267→  }\n   268→  if (!cachedNoiseRefEmbedding) {\n   269→    cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = await embed(NOISE_REFERENCE);\n   270→  }\n   271→\n   272→  // Find ALL_CAPS candidates with ≥2 words where every significant word has ≥4 alpha letters.\n   273→  // Insignificant tokens (≤1 alpha letter: \"/\", \"&\", \"+\", \":\", \"D)\", etc.) are filtered before\n   274→  // the check so that multi-line joins with continuation punctuation still qualify.\n   275→  const isStructuralHeading = (c: { text: string }): boolean => {\n   276→    if (!isAllCaps(c.text) || wordCount(c.text) < 2) return false;\n   277→    const sigWords = c.text.trim().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length > 1);\n   278→    return sigWords.length >= 2 && sigWords.every((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   279→  };\n   280→\n   281→  // Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates (embedding quality signal)\n   282→  const rawScored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; rawScore: number; embedding: Array<number> }> = [];\n   283→  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n   284→    const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n   285→    const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n   286→    const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n   287→    const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n   288→    const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n   289→    rawScored.push({ text: candidate.text, position: candidate.position, origin: candidate.origin, rawScore, embedding });\n   290→  }\n   291→\n   292→  // Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n   293→  // This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\n   294→  const structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\n   295→\n   296→  // Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n   297→  // if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled.\n   298→  for (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n   299→    const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   300→    for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n   301→      if (other === sc) continue;\n   302→      const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   303→      const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n   304→        otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n   305→      );\n   306→      if (hasTruncation) {\n   307→        sc.rawScore -= 0.15;\n   308→        break;\n   309→      }\n   310→    }\n   311→  }\n   312→\n   313→  const bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n   314→    ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n   315→    : null;\n   316→  const baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n   317→\n   318→  // When the best structural heading has a continuation on the next line introduced by a\n   319→  // punctuation token (/, &, +, :, or parenthesis), prefer the longer 2-line join as the\n   320→  // complete heading. E.g. \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" + \"/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\".\n   321→  // Guard: the remainder after the prefix must start with a continuation character to avoid\n   322→  // merging two separate consecutive recipe titles (FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS stays separate\n   323→  // from FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS because \"FINNISH\" does not start with a continuation token).\n   324→  const firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n   325→    rawScored.find((c) => {\n   326→      if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n   327→      const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   328→      const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n   329→      return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n   330→    }) ?? baseHeading\n   331→  );\n   332→\n   333→  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n   334→  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n   335→    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker — amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it\n   336→    const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n   337→    const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n   338→      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n   339→      : 1.0;\n   340→\n   341→    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings\n   342→    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   343→      ? 0.08\n   344→      : 0;\n   345→\n   346→    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n   347→    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n   348→\n   349→    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n   350→    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n   351→    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n   352→    // baseScore excludes position factor — used for diagnostics and ranking\n   353→    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   354→    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   355→    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n   356→  });\n   357→\n   358→  if (scored.length === 0) {\n   359→    return undefined;\n   360→  }\n   361→\n   362→  // Use thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) so the structural bonus doesn't inflate\n   363→  // the threshold and block equally-valid headings on multi-recipe pages.\n   364→  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n   365→  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n   366→\n   367→  // Filter candidates above threshold\n   368→  let selected = scored.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n   369→\n   370→  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n   371→  // the threshold. Cases:\n   372→  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n   373→  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n   374→  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n   375→  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n   376→  // Safety: only fires when the complete heading itself is in selected (passed the threshold).\n   377→  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text)) {\n   378→    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   379→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   380→      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) return true;\n   381→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   382→      // Remove s if it is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading\n   383→      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n   384→    });\n   385→  }\n   386→\n   387→  // Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join survived the threshold and its second\n   388→  // part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line prefix so the dedup\n   389→  // \"shorter wins\" rule doesn't destroy the complete join.\n   390→  // E.g. \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\" is removed when\n   391→  // \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" also survived (continuation: &).\n   392→  // Safety: only fires for joins whose continuation starts with /&+:( — digit continuations\n   393→  // like \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\" are NOT protected, so dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n   394→  const survivingJoins = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n   395→  if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n   396→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   397→      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n   398→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   399→      return !survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n   400→        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n   401→        if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n   402→        const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n   403→        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n   404→      });\n   405→    });\n   406→  }\n   407→\n   408→  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n   409→  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n   410→  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\".\n   411→  // The pre-filter above handles the conflicting case (structural heading prefix removal) so that\n   412→  // the incomplete prefix line is never present here when the complete join is in selected.\n   413→  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n   414→    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n   415→    return !selected.some(\n   416→      (b) =>\n   417→        b !== a &&\n   418→        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n   419→        b.text.length < a.text.length\n   420→    );\n   421→  });\n   422→\n   423→  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n   424→  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (≥2 ALL_CAPS headings).\n   425→  // A single ALL_CAPS title among mixed-case survivors is a single-recipe page —\n   426→  // collapse to the highest-scoring candidate.\n   427→  // Zero ALL_CAPS survivors → mixed-case multi-title page → keep all.\n   428→  if (selected.length > 1) {\n   429→    const allCapsSelected = selected.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text));\n   430→    if (allCapsSelected.length >= 2) {\n   431→      selected = allCapsSelected;\n   432→    } else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n   433→      selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   434→    }\n   435→  }\n   436→\n   437→  // Cap at 3, sort by document position\n   438→  selected.sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n   439→  selected = selected.slice(0, 3);\n   440→\n   441→  if (selected.length === 0) {\n   442→    return undefined;\n   443→  }\n   444→\n   445→  return selected.map((s) => s.text).join(\" + \");\n   446→}\n   447→\n   448→/**\n   449→ * Extract potential recipe title from OCR text (sync heuristic fallback)\n   450→ */\n   451→export function extractTitle(text: string): string | undefined {\n   452→  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n   453→    return undefined;\n   454→  }\n   455→\n   456→  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\").map((line) => line.trim());\n   457→\n   458→  for (const line of lines) {\n   459→    if (line.length === 0) continue;\n   460→    if (line.length < 3 || line.length > 50) continue;\n   461→    if (looksLikeIngredient(line)) continue;\n   462→    if (isAllCaps(line)) continue;\n   463→    if (startsWithNumber(line)) continue;\n   464→    return line;\n   465→  }\n   466→\n   467→  return undefined;\n   468→}\n   469→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"387de5e0-40bd-48c5-805c-791e6708a784","uuid":"d93e1f9f-0605-4013-be6b-05f209011b5d","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts","content":"/**\n * Title Extraction\n * Extracts potential recipe title from OCR text using heuristics or semantic embeddings\n */\n\nimport { cosineSimilarity } from \"./embeddings\";\n\nexport type EmbedFn = (text: string) => Promise<Array<number>>;\n\nconst TITLE_REFERENCE =\n  \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\";\nconst HEADER_REFERENCE =\n  \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\";\nconst NOISE_REFERENCE =\n  \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\";\n\n/**\n * Measurement units commonly found in ingredient lists\n */\nconst MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS = [\n  \"cup\",\n  \"cups\",\n  \"tbsp\",\n  \"tsp\",\n  \"tablespoon\",\n  \"teaspoon\",\n  \"oz\",\n  \"lb\",\n  \"gram\",\n  \"grams\",\n  \"kg\",\n  \"ml\",\n  \"liter\",\n  \"pinch\",\n  \"dash\",\n  \"handful\",\n];\n\n/**\n * Patterns that identify recipe metadata lines (not titles)\n */\nconst METADATA_PATTERNS = [\n  /^(SERVES?|MAKES?|YIELDS?)\\b/i,\n  /^(PREP(ARATION)?|COOK(ING)?|PROOF|RISING|FERMENTATION|REST(ING)?)\\s*(AND\\s*)?(COOK(ING)?)?\\s*TIME/i,\n  /^SAMPLE\\s+SCHEDULE\\b/i,\n  /^BULK\\s+FERMENTATION\\b/i,\n  /^(THIS\\s+RECIPE\\s+)?MAKES\\b/i,\n];\n\n/**\n * Single-word non-title words — standalone OCR fragments unlikely to be recipe titles\n */\nconst NON_TITLE_WORDS = new Set([\n  \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"are\", \"was\",\n  \"has\", \"his\", \"her\", \"its\", \"our\", \"who\", \"how\", \"may\", \"new\", \"now\",\n  \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\", \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n  \"buns\", \"with\",\n]);\n\nfunction looksLikeIngredient(line: string): boolean {\n  const lowerLine = line.toLowerCase();\n  return MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => lowerLine.includes(pattern));\n}\n\nfunction startsWithNumber(line: string): boolean {\n  return /^\\s*\\d/.test(line);\n}\n\nfunction isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n}\n\nfunction looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n}\n\nfunction isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n  if (letters.length < 2) return true;\n\n  // Check vowel ratio — English/Polish text typically has 30–50% vowels\n  const vowels = letters.replace(/[^aeiouAEIOUyYąęóĄĘÓ]/g, \"\").length;\n  const vowelRatio = vowels / letters.length;\n  if (vowelRatio < 0.15 || vowelRatio > 0.85) return true;\n\n  // Single orphaned word ≤3 letters that isn't a common word\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  const COMMON_SHORT = new Set([\n    \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"had\", \"her\",\n    \"was\", \"one\", \"our\", \"out\", \"are\", \"has\", \"his\", \"how\", \"its\", \"may\",\n    \"new\", \"now\", \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"who\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\",\n    \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n  ]);\n  if (words.length === 1 && letters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Recipe titles never start with a lowercase letter\n  if (/^[a-z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Mid-text sentence boundary (\". \" followed by a letter) — body text fragment spliced from multiple sentences\n  const trimmed = text.trim();\n  if (/\\.\\s+[a-zA-Z]/.test(trimmed) && !trimmed.endsWith(\")\")) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Multi-word candidate containing a garbled OCR fragment: a short lowercase word that isn't a known short word\n  if (words.length >= 2) {\n    const commonShort2 = new Set([\n      \"a\", \"i\", \"of\", \"or\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"is\", \"it\", \"an\",\n      \"as\", \"at\", \"by\", \"do\", \"go\", \"if\", \"no\", \"so\", \"up\", \"we\",\n      \"w\", \"z\",  // Polish prepositions\n    ]);\n    const hasGarbledWord = words.some(\n      (w) =>\n        /^[a-z]/.test(w) &&\n        w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\").length <= 2 &&\n        !commonShort2.has(w.toLowerCase())\n    );\n    if (hasGarbledWord) {\n      return true;\n    }\n  }\n\n  return false;\n}\n\nfunction passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n  // Single-word non-title fragments\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  if (words.length === 1 && NON_TITLE_WORDS.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) return false;\n  return true;\n}\n\n/**\n * Detect initial burst of short garbled lines.\n * Returns the index of the first non-garbled or long line.\n */\nfunction findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n  let i = 0;\n  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text)) {\n    i++;\n  }\n  return i;\n}\n\nfunction wordCount(text: string): number {\n  return text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 0).length;\n}\n\n/**\n * Build candidate strings from lines: single lines plus multi-line joins (2-3 consecutive).\n * Skips initial burst of short garbled lines. Scans all remaining lines. Caps at 25.\n */\nexport type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n\nfunction buildCandidates(\n  lines: Array<string>\n): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n\n  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n    }\n  }\n\n  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n  const candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> = [];\n  const seen = new Set<string>();\n\n  for (let i = burstEnd; i < nonEmptyLines.length; i++) {\n    const line = nonEmptyLines[i];\n\n    // Single line\n    if (passesHardFilters(line.text)) {\n      const norm = line.text.toLowerCase();\n      if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n        seen.add(norm);\n        candidates.push({ text: line.text, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 2-line join\n    if (i + 1 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n      const joined2 = `${line.text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text}`;\n      if (passesHardFilters(joined2)) {\n        const norm = joined2.toLowerCase();\n        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n          seen.add(norm);\n          candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 3-line join\n    if (i + 2 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n      const joined3 = `${line.text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text} ${nonEmptyLines[i + 2].text}`;\n      if (passesHardFilters(joined3)) {\n        const norm = joined3.toLowerCase();\n        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n          seen.add(norm);\n          candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Pre-filter to 25 before embedding calls: prefer ALL_CAPS and short candidates.\n  // Position-based scoring handles final ranking.\n  if (candidates.length > 25) {\n    const prioritized = candidates.slice().sort((a, b) => {\n      const aAllCaps = isAllCaps(a.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      const bAllCaps = isAllCaps(b.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      if (aAllCaps !== bAllCaps) return aAllCaps - bAllCaps;\n      const aShort = wordCount(a.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      const bShort = wordCount(b.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      return aShort - bShort;\n    });\n    return prioritized.slice(0, 25);\n  }\n\n  return candidates;\n}\n\n// Module-level cache for reference embeddings\nlet cachedTitleRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\nlet cachedHeaderRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\nlet cachedNoiseRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n\nexport function _resetEmbeddingCacheForTests(): void {\n  cachedTitleRefEmbedding = null;\n  cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = null;\n  cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = null;\n}\n\nexport async function extractTitleWithEmbeddings(\n  text: string,\n  embed: EmbedFn\n): Promise<string | undefined> {\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\");\n  const candidates = buildCandidates(lines);\n\n  if (candidates.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  // Cache reference embeddings\n  if (!cachedTitleRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedTitleRefEmbedding = await embed(TITLE_REFERENCE);\n  }\n  if (!cachedHeaderRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = await embed(HEADER_REFERENCE);\n  }\n  if (!cachedNoiseRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = await embed(NOISE_REFERENCE);\n  }\n\n  // Find ALL_CAPS candidates with ≥2 words where every significant word has ≥4 alpha letters.\n  // Insignificant tokens (≤1 alpha letter: \"/\", \"&\", \"+\", \":\", \"D)\", etc.) are filtered before\n  // the check so that multi-line joins with continuation punctuation still qualify.\n  const isStructuralHeading = (c: { text: string }): boolean => {\n    if (!isAllCaps(c.text) || wordCount(c.text) < 2) return false;\n    const sigWords = c.text.trim().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length > 1);\n    return sigWords.length >= 2 && sigWords.every((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n  };\n\n  // Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates (embedding quality signal)\n  const rawScored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; rawScore: number; embedding: Array<number> }> = [];\n  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n    const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n    const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n    const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n    const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n    const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n    rawScored.push({ text: candidate.text, position: candidate.position, origin: candidate.origin, rawScore, embedding });\n  }\n\n  // Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n  // This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\n  const structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\n\n  // Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n  // if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled.\n  for (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n    const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n    for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n      if (other === sc) continue;\n      const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n      const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n        otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n      );\n      if (hasTruncation) {\n        sc.rawScore -= 0.15;\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  const bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n    ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => a.rawScore > b.rawScore ? a : b)\n    : null;\n  const baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n\n  // When the best structural heading has a continuation on the next line introduced by a\n  // punctuation token (/, &, +, :, or parenthesis), prefer the longer 2-line join as the\n  // complete heading. E.g. \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" + \"/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\".\n  // Guard: the remainder after the prefix must start with a continuation character to avoid\n  // merging two separate consecutive recipe titles (FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS stays separate\n  // from FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS because \"FINNISH\" does not start with a continuation token).\n  const firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n    rawScored.find((c) => {\n      if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n      const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n      const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n      return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n    }) ?? baseHeading\n  );\n\n  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker — amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it\n    const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n    const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n      : 1.0;\n\n    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings\n    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n      ? 0.08\n      : 0;\n\n    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n\n    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n    // baseScore excludes position factor — used for diagnostics and ranking\n    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n  });\n\n  if (scored.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  // Use thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) so the structural bonus doesn't inflate\n  // the threshold and block equally-valid headings on multi-recipe pages.\n  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scored.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n\n  // Filter candidates above threshold\n  let selected = scored.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n\n  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n  // the threshold. Cases:\n  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n  // Safety: only fires when the complete heading itself is in selected (passed the threshold).\n  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text)) {\n    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      // Remove s if it is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading\n      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join survived the threshold and its second\n  // part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line prefix so the dedup\n  // \"shorter wins\" rule doesn't destroy the complete join.\n  // E.g. \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce\" is removed when\n  // \"Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander\" also survived (continuation: &).\n  // Safety: only fires for joins whose continuation starts with /&+:( — digit continuations\n  // like \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\" are NOT protected, so dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n  const survivingJoins = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n  if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      return !survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n        if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n        const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n      });\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\".\n  // The pre-filter above handles the conflicting case (structural heading prefix removal) so that\n  // the incomplete prefix line is never present here when the complete join is in selected.\n  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n    return !selected.some(\n      (b) =>\n        b !== a &&\n        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n        b.text.length < a.text.length\n    );\n  });\n\n  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (≥2 ALL_CAPS headings).\n  // A single ALL_CAPS title among mixed-case survivors is a single-recipe page —\n  // collapse to the highest-scoring candidate.\n  // Zero ALL_CAPS survivors → mixed-case multi-title page → keep all.\n  if (selected.length > 1) {\n    const allCapsSelected = selected.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text));\n    if (allCapsSelected.length >= 2) {\n      selected = allCapsSelected;\n    } else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n      selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Cap at 3, sort by document position\n  selected.sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n  selected = selected.slice(0, 3);\n\n  if (selected.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  return selected.map((s) => s.text).join(\" + \");\n}\n\n/**\n * Extract potential recipe title from OCR text (sync heuristic fallback)\n */\nexport function extractTitle(text: string): string | undefined {\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\").map((line) => line.trim());\n\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    if (line.length === 0) continue;\n    if (line.length < 3 || line.length > 50) continue;\n    if (looksLikeIngredient(line)) continue;\n    if (isAllCaps(line)) continue;\n    if (startsWithNumber(line)) continue;\n    return line;\n  }\n\n  return undefined;\n}\n","numLines":469,"startLine":1,"totalLines":469}}}
